}\tab{\b0 ({\*\bkmkstart BMass_errors}2{\*\bkmkend BMass_errors})}}\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs24\sl360\slmult1 \fi360 As it is pointed out by Baltagi ({2008}), beyond the consideration of endogeneity issues with {{\i h}}, the introduction of a lag of the dependent variable in ({\field{\*\fldinst{\lang1024 REF BMmodel \\* MERGEFORMAT }}{\fldrslt{1}}}) yields a situation known as {\i dynamic panel bias}. For instance, since {{\field{\*\fldinst{ EQ {\i y}\\s\\do6({\fs20 {\i i}{\i t}})}}{\fldrslt }}
