\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs24\sl360\slmult1 \fi360 Two approaches that follow the generalized-method-of-moments developed by 
(Hansen, {1982}
) to overcome the {\i dynamic panel bias} are the Difference GMM estimator, proposed by Holtz-Eakin et al. ({1988}) and Arellano and{} Bond ({1991}) in which the data is converted using the first-difference transformation{\cs62\super\chftn}
{\*\footnote\pard \s65\ql\fi-113\li397\lin397\f0\fs24{\cs62\super\chftn} The first-difference transformation is performed by multiplying {{\field{\*\fldinst{ EQ {\i y}\\s\\do6({\fs20 {\i i}{\i t}})={\u945*}{\i y}\\s\\do6({\fs20 {\i i}{\i t}\u8722?1})+{\u946*}{\i x}\\s\\do6({\fs20 {\i i}{\i t}})+{\u956*}\\s\\do6({\fs20 {\i i}})+{\i v}\\s\\do6({\fs20 {\i i}{\i t}})}}{\fldrslt }}
