\pard\plain\s3\ql\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\b\fs32\sl240\slmult1 \sb240 \fi0 Appendix: System GMM estimator\par
{\*\bkmkstart BMsystemGMM}{\*\bkmkend BMsystemGMM}\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs24\sl240\slmult1 \sb60 \fi0 We estimate a dynamic panel data model by using the System GMM estimator developed by Arellano and Bover (1995) and Blundell and Bond (1998) based on the Difference GMM estimator proposed earlier by Holtz-Eakin et al. (1988) and Arellano and Bond (1991). Both, Difference and System GMM estimators are specific applications of the generalized-method-of-moments (Hansen, 1982). In this section we explain the underlying details of the estimator in five steps. First, we outline a simple autoregressive panel data model and review inconsistency issues of common estimators. Second, considering the same simple autoregressive model, we explain the Difference GMM estimator. Third, we go further to construct the System GMM estimator. Fourth, we extend the explanation to multivariate models. Finally, we outline some issues about the conditions for optimality of the System GMM estimator and relevant tests. In most of the explanation we follow rigorous surveys of Difference and System GMM estimators made by Arellano and Honore (2001), Blundell et al. (2000) and Bond (2002).\par
